  "body": "I noticed the following bugs while using `hardhat-node`: \r\n\r\n- `npx hardhat node --network localhost` :\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36712489/103292879-08e26c00-49ef-11eb-83a9-8087c5987388.png)\r\n\r\nWeirdly the error changes when `localhost` is the `defaultNetwork` - I would have expected the same error. \r\n\r\n- defaultNetwork: \"localhost\" \r\n  - `npx hardhat node`\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36712489/103292979-3e875500-49ef-11eb-8303-ce9a5b90a5c7.png)\r\n\r\n==> It only seems to work if --network hardhat is passed or if defaultNetwork is empty / \"hardhat\"\r\n\r\nNow the more serious bugs: \r\n\r\n- defaultNetwork: \"ropsten\" \r\n  - `npx hardhat node` \r\n  \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36712489/103293223-bbb2ca00-49ef-11eb-827d-f3907609806b.png)\r\n\r\nAs you can see I am using `hardhat-deploy` which overrides the `hardhat node` task to run deploy scripts on start. I accidentally had my `defaultNetwork:` set to `ropsten` and somehow the `hardhat node` task did not fail and it deployed contracts to ropsten. \r\n\r\n**I would have expected `hardhat node` to fail with a Hardhat error similar to** `Error HH605: Unsupported network for JSON-RPC server.`\r\n\r\nThis works when `--network ropsten` is passed as a flag:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36712489/103293723-b3a75a00-49f0-11eb-8e3b-096810bee84c.png)\r\n\r\n**But apparently not if the network is configured as defaultNetwork.**\r\n\r\n",
